Reboot Multiple Dell Servers via iDRAC (IPMI) Using a Bash Script
==================================================================

This script automates rebooting Dell servers using their iDRAC (IPMI) interfaces, especially useful during outages when the server OS is unresponsive but the iDRAC remains accessible.

Features
========

Batch Processing: Reboot multiple servers simultaneously or in custom batch sizes.

Error Logging: Logs servers that failed to reboot for follow-up actions.

Ease of Use: Provides a simple way to input server lists and credentials.

What the Script Does
=====================

Reads the server list from hostList.txt.

Connects to each server's iDRAC and issues a serveraction powercycle command.

Logs any servers that fail to reboot in failed_hosts.txt

This script simplifies server management during critical times, ensuring quicker recovery and reduced manual effort.
